<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-02-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-02-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="437" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d437">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 4001/66.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">British Chargé</gloss> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">British
                                        Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-02-01"><hi rend="italic">February 1,
                                1907</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 28.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you, in
                            accordance with instructions received from Sir Edward Grey, that the
                            governor of Jamaica desires that an expression of his most sincere
                            thanks, which are very cordially indorsed by His Majesty’s Government,
                            should be conveyed to the United States Government for a supply of tents
                            which have been just received in Jamaica.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Esme Howard.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>